premise_source_doc_sentence: ESPN GamePlan was an out-of-market sports package offering college football games to viewers throughout the United States .

On August 28 , 2015 , the package was discontinued , along with ESPN Full Court , to make way for ESPN College Extra , which will offer a select bundle of games that would previously have been broadcast by GamePlan and Full Court .

Eventually though , with carriage of ESPN3 moving from computers only to smartphones , tablets and digital media players allowing access without any additional fees , GamePlan became a superfluous package , with only the few providers who refused to offer ESPN3 or where ESPN3 access was limited  (  for instance , rural areas  )  really able to compel viewers to utilize the service .
GamePlan began on Labor Day weekend , and continued through the first Saturday in December .
